dct_title_s: Map of Pennsylvania and New Jersey
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. In upper margin: American atlas. Shows roads, towns, villages, mills, iron works, forts, post offices, battle grounds, places of worship, public houses, and ferries. "Entered according to Act of Congress, the 20th day of August 1823, by H.S. Tanner, of the State of Pennsylvania." "Engraved by H.S. Tanner & assistants." From: A new American atlas containing maps of the several states of the North American union ... Philadelphia : H.S. Tanner, 1823.
